properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 11 at 3:08PM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...PERIOD OF GUSTY NORTH WINDS EXPECTED WEDNESDAY NIGHT AND
THURSDAY...

* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
waves 7 to 12 feet possible.

* WHERE...Southern Open Waters of Lake Michigan.

* WHEN...From late Wednesday night through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
